Ladonia is an unincorporated community located in the Franklin Township of northwest Surry County, North Carolina.  The community generally lies on the Fisher River and is centered on the intersection of Blevins Store Road and Ladonia Church Road (Powell 1968, p. 267).  Area landmarks include Ladonia Baptist Church, M & M Signs and Awnings (right at the intersection of the two roads), and the nearby Raven Knob Scout Reservation.


== References ==
Powell, William S. (1968), The North Carolina Gazetteer:  A Dictionary of Tar Heel Places, Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina Press, ISBN 0-8078-1247-1